    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed with a three-part structure to facilitate easy learning and reference: 1) 'Understand the Risks' for foundational knowledge, 2) 'Prevention Checklists' for actionable advice, and 3) 'Key Statistics' for data-driven insights. This thematic grouping, navigated by a sticky header, allows users to explore content non-linearly based on their immediate needs (e.g., a manager might jump to checklists, while a new employee might start with definitions). This is more user-centric than the linear flow of the source document, promoting better engagement and retention. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Definitions of Slip, Trip, Fall. Goal: Inform/Compare. Method: Three-column card layout (Tailwind Grid). Interaction: N/A, layout provides clarity. Justification: Side-by-side comparison enhances understanding of distinct concepts. Library: HTML/Tailwind.
        - Report Info: Prevention Methods. Goal: Organize/Action. Method: Interactive toggle buttons revealing checklists. Interaction: JS-powered show/hide functionality. Justification: Reduces cognitive load by presenting one checklist at a time, making the advice feel more manageable and tool-like. Library: Vanilla JS.
        - Report Info: Fall Statistics (67%/33%). Goal: Emphasize. Method: Donut Chart. Interaction: Hover tooltips for precise data. Justification: A visual chart provides a much stronger impact for proportional data than text alone. Library: Chart.js (Canvas).
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
